<TITLE> Two dead bodies found at bus ticket counter </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 16 (bdnews24.com)  Police on Tuesday recovered two dead bodies from a bus ticket counter of a transport agency in the capital's Arambagh. One of the deceased was identified as, Ilias, 19, the clerk of the counter while the other could not be identified, police said. Matijheel thana police sub-inspector Mokarram Hossain told bdnews24.com that the bodies were recovered from a ticket office run jointly by S Alam and Saudia transport agencies at Arambagh. He said a ticket counter official, Hanif, had left for home at 2 am leaving Ilias and two passengers at the counter. But when Hanif came back later in the morning, he found the main gate closed. As nobody answered from inside the counter, Hanif became suspicious and informed the police, the police officer said. Police then broke down the doors and recovered the bodies from inside, he said. Hossain said nothing was stolen from the bus counter and police were trying to get information on the two passengers who were there earlier in the morning. b
